17
00:00:12,297 --> 00:00:12,414
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,415 --> 00:00:15,415
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,441
<i>invasion in peril!</i>

20
00:00:20,983 --> 00:00:23,236
<i>Republic forces struggle to take Um bar a,</i>

21
00:00:23,319 --> 00:00:26,614
<i>a hostile planet
completely enshrouded in darkness.</i>

22
00:00:26,864 --> 00:00:29,408
<i>Jedi General Pong Krell and Captain Rex</i>

23
00:00:29,450 --> 00:00:33,246
<i>lead a battalion against a constant attack
by a brutal enemy.</i>

24
00:00:33,454 --> 00:00:36,123
<i>Krell's aggressive
and reckless strategies backfire,</i>

25
00:00:36,165 --> 00:00:37,458
<i>killing many clones.</i>

26
00:00:38,042 --> 00:00:40,545
<i>Despite the Jedi General's
dangerous tactics,</i>

27
00:00:40,628 --> 00:00:43,965
<i>Captain Rex's squad
successfully captures a critical airbase.</i>

28
00:00:44,298 --> 00:00:47,635
<i>This further fuels
the mistrust of Krell's leadership,</i>

29
00:00:47,718 --> 00:00:49,595
<i>dividing his men.</i>

30
00:01:03,192 --> 00:01:05,653
The insurgents
have stepped up their attacks, sir.

31
00:01:05,695 --> 00:01:07,446
They want their base back.

32
00:01:07,488 --> 00:01:09,699
We cannot let our guard down
for a moment.

33
00:01:10,032 --> 00:01:13,202
Have all Um bar an security
re-configured and locked down.

34
00:01:13,286 --> 00:01:15,621
Interrogate the prisoners if you have to,

35
00:01:15,663 --> 00:01:18,624
but I want this base
under our complete control

36
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,418
and I don't want excuses.

37
00:01:20,751 --> 00:01:23,296
Sir, there's a transmission
from General Kenobi.

38
00:01:23,629 --> 00:01:25,506
I'll take it in the tower.

39
00:01:31,846 --> 00:01:33,681
Hey, how's it coming?

40
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:36,350
Tricky piece of hardware.

41
00:01:36,726 --> 00:01:39,020
Krell's got Jesse stacking ordnance.

42
00:01:41,355 --> 00:01:45,026
I'm still waiting for Krell to thank us
for handing this base over to him.

43
00:01:50,656 --> 00:01:51,657
Where is he?

44
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:55,870
General Kenobi, do you read me?

45
00:01:55,911 --> 00:01:59,206
<i>Congratulations on your capture
of the Um bar an airbase, General.</i>

46
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:01,542
<i>It's refreshing to have good news.</i>

47
00:02:01,584 --> 00:02:04,754
There will be time for celebration
when we've taken that capital.

48
00:02:05,046 --> 00:02:08,758
<i>Yes. Well, I'm afraid that's
going to be more difficult than anticipated.</i>

49
00:02:08,841 --> 00:02:10,092
<i>Their attacks have increased</i>

50
00:02:10,217 --> 00:02:12,762
<i>and their long-range missiles
are forcing us to retreat</i>

51
00:02:12,845 --> 00:02:14,221
<i>from our positions.</i>

52
00:02:14,263 --> 00:02:17,058
I was hoping we cut off
their arms shipments and supplies

53
00:02:17,141 --> 00:02:18,517
when we took this airbase.

54
00:02:18,809 --> 00:02:20,936
<i>It seems they're receiving
new arms shipments</i>

55
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:23,230
<i>directly from a supply ship orbiting...</i>

56
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:24,899
General Kenobi?

57
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:27,068
<i>We've been having difficulty transmitting...</i>

58
00:02:27,234 --> 00:02:28,944
<i>They must be jamming our signals.</i>

59
00:02:29,236 --> 00:02:30,821
Can't we destroy the supply ship?

60
00:02:31,113 --> 00:02:33,532
<i>We're trying, but with little success.</i>

61
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:35,242
<i>Their fleet outnumbers ours</i>

62
00:02:35,326 --> 00:02:38,037
<i>and the extra ships we were promised
have not yet arrived.</i>

63
00:02:38,412 --> 00:02:41,749
We'll just have to take that capital
regardless of the missiles.

64
00:02:41,832 --> 00:02:44,335
My battalion will meet you
at the rendezvous coordinates.

65
00:02:44,669 --> 00:02:46,462
<i>We cannot expect...</i>

66
00:02:47,713 --> 00:02:49,006
I'm trying to get him back, sir.

67
00:02:49,382 --> 00:02:53,094
Don't bother.
The enemy is jamming our transmissions.

68
00:02:53,177 --> 00:02:54,595
We are on our own.

69
00:03:05,272 --> 00:03:08,567
Have those containers searched
and all weapons prepped and loaded.

70
00:03:08,609 --> 00:03:11,112
Have the battalion ready to move out
in 12 hours.

71
00:03:11,195 --> 00:03:12,530
We're advancing on the capital.

72
00:03:12,863 --> 00:03:15,616
Sir, shall I try to get a message
to General Kenobi?

73
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:19,203
Shouldn't we coordinate our attack,
especially in light of the recent threat?

74
00:03:19,495 --> 00:03:22,373
General Kenobi has his hands full,
same as us.

75
00:03:22,456 --> 00:03:25,209
We need to throw everything we have
at them, now!

76
00:03:25,459 --> 00:03:28,295
We'd be marching into a blast zone, sir.

77
00:03:30,339 --> 00:03:32,133
Blasted insurgents.

78
00:03:34,468 --> 00:03:37,888
I realize you haven't agreed
with all my strategies, Captain.

79
00:03:37,972 --> 00:03:41,642
But you are smart enough
and loyal enough to obey my orders.

80
00:03:42,101 --> 00:03:44,019
Now, prep those troops!

81
00:03:54,739 --> 00:03:59,326
Those missiles have 100 megaton yield.
We won't even make it to the delta.

82
00:03:59,660 --> 00:04:00,995
What can I do?

83
00:04:01,078 --> 00:04:03,998
I've tried to reason with him.
Those are the orders.

84
00:04:04,081 --> 00:04:06,375
Great. Another suicide mission.

85
00:04:06,459 --> 00:04:08,252
The capital is too well armed.

86
00:04:08,335 --> 00:04:10,713
Why does it seem like
he has it out for clones?

87
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,882
I think you're all overreacting.

88
00:04:12,965 --> 00:04:15,509
Obviously,
General Krell knows what he's doing.

89
00:04:15,551 --> 00:04:18,429
Do you really think
he doesn't care if he loses men?

90
00:04:18,512 --> 00:04:19,972
I'm not saying that.

91
00:04:20,014 --> 00:04:23,017
But I do think his desire for victory
has blinded him to the fact

92
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,811
that there are lives at stake.

93
00:04:25,853 --> 00:04:28,856
I've never seen a general
with these kinds of casualties.

94
00:04:28,898 --> 00:04:32,443
He's out of control !
He's not acting like the other Jedi.

95
00:04:32,526 --> 00:04:33,944
He has no respect for us.

96
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:38,365
Listen, I don't agree with him either,
but I don't have a better plan.

97
00:04:38,783 --> 00:04:41,827
What about using these star fighters
to destroy the supply ship?

98
00:04:41,994 --> 00:04:43,370
Our fleet has been trying.

99
00:04:43,537 --> 00:04:46,207
The Umbarans have it as protected
as the capital.

100
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:49,710
But we've got their access codes
and their own hardware.

101
00:04:50,002 --> 00:04:51,086
You were able to crack it?

102
00:04:51,253 --> 00:04:52,463
Mmm-hmm.

103
00:04:52,546 --> 00:04:57,051
We can sneak right past their blockade,
get where our ships can't.

104
00:04:59,053 --> 00:05:03,516
If we take out that supply ship,
then we cut off arms to the capital.

105
00:05:12,399 --> 00:05:14,902
Sir, with all due respect,

106
00:05:14,944 --> 00:05:18,364
might I suggest another option
to help us secure the capital?

107
00:05:18,739 --> 00:05:20,449
What would that be, Captain?

108
00:05:20,741 --> 00:05:23,160
My men have cracked the Um bar an codes.

109
00:05:23,244 --> 00:05:27,414
With the star fighters, we can sneak past
the supply ship's defenses.

110
00:05:27,498 --> 00:05:30,709
We take it out,
we cut off the arms to the capital.

111
00:05:31,418 --> 00:05:34,755
And who do you propose
would fly these star fighters?

112
00:05:34,797 --> 00:05:36,924
Are your troops now pilots?

113
00:05:37,591 --> 00:05:39,593
My men may not be pilots, sir,

114
00:05:39,677 --> 00:05:42,805
but they are able to learn
and adapt quickly.

115
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:45,182
A few of them
have already demonstrated that.

116
00:05:45,808 --> 00:05:49,979
I'm afraid I can't afford to waste any clones
on frivolous adventures.

117
00:05:50,646 --> 00:05:54,692
We're going to need everyone
to take the capital.

118
00:05:54,775 --> 00:05:57,736
Sir, incoming. Sector delta.
Long-range missiles.

119
00:06:18,883 --> 00:06:21,969
The assault on the capital

120
00:06:22,052 --> 00:06:23,429
will continue as planned.

121
00:06:23,971 --> 00:06:27,433
So that's it?
We just march into those missiles?

122
00:06:28,183 --> 00:06:29,727
Oh, there's another option.

123
00:06:29,810 --> 00:06:33,188
We go ahead with our plan,
and suffer the consequences.

124
00:06:33,689 --> 00:06:36,650
You would be court-martialed.

125
00:06:36,734 --> 00:06:39,486
If it were up to me,
and we had the time and the training,

126
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:41,822
I would say, "Do it."

127
00:06:41,864 --> 00:06:45,576
But it's out of my hands and the truth is,
you are no pilots.

128
00:06:45,868 --> 00:06:48,996
Come on.
If Hard case can fly one of these things,

129
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,414
we all can.

130
00:06:50,497 --> 00:06:54,418
Yeah, he wasn't really flying.
More like avoiding crashing.

131
00:06:54,752 --> 00:06:57,004
We'll be blasted out of the sky
before we get anywhere.

132
00:06:57,338 --> 00:07:01,675
Not if we're in their fighters.
No one's gonna be shooting at us.

133
00:07:03,594 --> 00:07:05,471
Here comes Dogma.

134
00:07:05,679 --> 00:07:07,473
Uh... What's going on?

135
00:07:08,015 --> 00:07:09,850
Er... Nothing.

136
00:07:19,151 --> 00:07:21,737
This is about
more than just following orders.

137
00:07:22,237 --> 00:07:24,531
It is. It is about honor.

138
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:28,118
Where is the honor
in marching blindly to our deaths?

139
00:07:28,702 --> 00:07:30,704
It is not our call.

140
00:07:30,788 --> 00:07:32,790
We are part of something larger.

141
00:07:32,873 --> 00:07:34,667
We're not independent of one another.

142
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:39,129
I'm sorry. I cannot just follow orders
when I know they're wrong.

143
00:07:39,213 --> 00:07:41,131
Especially when lives are at stake.

144
00:07:41,715 --> 00:07:45,511
You will if you support
the system we fight for.

145
00:07:45,803 --> 00:07:48,305
I do support it. I do!

146
00:07:48,389 --> 00:07:51,809
But I am not just another number!
None of us are!

147
00:07:52,142 --> 00:07:53,435
Fives, where are you going?

148
00:07:54,228 --> 00:07:56,271
To round up some pilots.

149
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:12,538
All right.

150
00:08:12,579 --> 00:08:14,498
Okay, there. Try that out.

151
00:08:14,748 --> 00:08:16,166
It should be a little easier.

152
00:08:21,755 --> 00:08:22,756
I got it.

153
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,386
Whoa!

154
00:08:31,932 --> 00:08:33,600
Hard case, what are you doing?

155
00:08:34,018 --> 00:08:35,728
If I knew, I wouldn't be doing it!

156
00:08:39,106 --> 00:08:40,274
Look out!

157
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:45,112
Great. This can't get much worse.

158
00:08:50,617 --> 00:08:54,288
Sir, there appears to be a disturbance
in Hangar 9-4.

159
00:08:56,206 --> 00:08:58,375
Trooper, what's going on down there?

160
00:08:58,792 --> 00:09:00,794
Hey, hey, I got this.

161
00:09:00,836 --> 00:09:02,463
<i>Report, Trooper.</i>

162
00:09:02,546 --> 00:09:05,674
Er... Yes, sir.
Everything's fine in the hangar, sir.

163
00:09:05,758 --> 00:09:06,967
Nothing's out of control down here.

164
00:09:07,051 --> 00:09:09,636
<i>Then why have
the alarms been triggered?</i>

165
00:09:11,805 --> 00:09:13,807
<i>It's just a drill, a safety drill, sir.</i>

166
00:09:13,891 --> 00:09:17,561
Safety check occurs at 0600.
Who authorized this drill?

167
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:19,104
Uh...

168
00:09:19,146 --> 00:09:22,858
We are decrypting the alien hardware, sir.

169
00:09:22,941 --> 00:09:24,485
Standard operating procedure.

170
00:09:27,237 --> 00:09:28,322
That didn't work.

171
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,994
Who is this? What's your CT number?

172
00:09:37,998 --> 00:09:39,625
<i>Trooper, identify yourself!</i>

173
00:09:39,917 --> 00:09:41,794
Okay. How about this?

174
00:09:44,671 --> 00:09:45,964
No, no, no, no, no.

175
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,261
That's gonna leave a mark.

176
00:10:01,855 --> 00:10:03,690
I'm going down there.

177
00:10:06,902 --> 00:10:10,697
Got it. I got it. It's easy.
Just level your hands.

178
00:10:15,619 --> 00:10:18,288
What, are you crazy?
You could've gotten us killed.

179
00:10:18,539 --> 00:10:21,208
Not to mention
ruining our hopes of flying this mission!

180
00:10:21,875 --> 00:10:24,461
It's a malfunction, no harm done.

181
00:10:24,545 --> 00:10:26,547
Explain this. Now.

182
00:10:28,674 --> 00:10:31,969
Sir, we were decrypting the enemy craft

183
00:10:32,052 --> 00:10:35,305
when what appears to be
an enemy booby trap went off.

184
00:10:35,722 --> 00:10:37,141
A booby trap?

185
00:10:37,558 --> 00:10:39,893
Yes, sir. The fighter went haywire

186
00:10:39,935 --> 00:10:44,231
and had I not been able to get control of it,
and aim the missile at the doors,

187
00:10:44,314 --> 00:10:46,650
something worse might've happened.

188
00:10:47,484 --> 00:10:48,902
Is this true?

189
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:53,240
Yes, sir. That is what happened, no doubt.

190
00:10:55,492 --> 00:10:58,203
Well, Captain Rex, looks like I was correct.

191
00:10:58,537 --> 00:11:00,664
The Um bar an fighters are dangerous

192
00:11:00,914 --> 00:11:02,249
and not fit for flight.

193
00:11:02,499 --> 00:11:06,587
But, sir, we now know how they work.
We just need practice!

194
00:11:08,505 --> 00:11:10,632
Lock down these fighters.

195
00:11:10,716 --> 00:11:12,801
I don't want anything else exploding.

196
00:11:15,137 --> 00:11:16,305
Nice work.

197
00:11:16,388 --> 00:11:19,933
Now we know how to fly them,
and we won't be able to get near them.

198
00:11:20,017 --> 00:11:23,979
Oh, come on. That won't stop us.
It's just procedure.

199
00:11:24,062 --> 00:11:28,066
We can sneak in and be out
before Krell knows anything.

200
00:11:29,902 --> 00:11:33,488
I thought the plan was to destroy
the enemy ship with the fighters,

201
00:11:33,572 --> 00:11:35,282
not blow up our own hangar.

202
00:11:35,616 --> 00:11:37,951
Look, I agree we should
go through with this.

203
00:11:38,035 --> 00:11:40,412
So, are you two volunteering
to be my pilots or what?

204
00:11:40,787 --> 00:11:43,916
I'm in regardless of the consequences.

205
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:47,002
Flying these fighters beats
blindly walking into a bunch of missiles,

206
00:11:47,085 --> 00:11:50,505
so, I'm in. We just need a plan.

207
00:11:50,714 --> 00:11:52,049
Already got one.

208
00:11:52,132 --> 00:11:55,510
General Skywalker blew up
a droid control ship when he was just a kid.

209
00:11:55,636 --> 00:12:00,140
And he told me the trick was hitting
the main reactor from the inside.

210
00:12:00,265 --> 00:12:01,308
Oh.

211
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:03,727
Well, that won't be so tough.

212
00:12:09,566 --> 00:12:11,151
I want a full perimeter sweep.

213
00:12:11,568 --> 00:12:13,487
Be on high alert.

214
00:12:17,324 --> 00:12:20,744
Fives, what are you doing out here?
You should be in the barracks.

215
00:12:21,161 --> 00:12:24,248
I found my pilots.
We're going after that supply ship.

216
00:12:24,665 --> 00:12:26,458
Are you out of your mind?

217
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,503
It's a suicide mission,
not to mention against orders.

218
00:12:29,753 --> 00:12:31,546
It's the right thing to do.

219
00:12:31,922 --> 00:12:33,382
We have to try.

220
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:37,469
It sounds like you intend
to go through with it.

221
00:12:37,844 --> 00:12:40,931
If you're going to try to stop us,
we need to know.

222
00:12:43,517 --> 00:12:45,852
I can't help you when you get caught.

223
00:12:46,603 --> 00:12:48,480
I understand, sir.

224
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:36,069
Hey. Hey, Tup.

225
00:13:36,153 --> 00:13:37,529
Wake up!

226
00:13:38,822 --> 00:13:41,158
What? I'm trying to sleep.

227
00:13:41,950 --> 00:13:43,118
Where are they?

228
00:13:44,244 --> 00:13:45,954
-Who?
-You know.

229
00:13:47,956 --> 00:13:50,459
Don't tell me
they're going to disobey orders.

230
00:13:51,001 --> 00:13:53,545
Well, I didn't say that.

231
00:13:56,298 --> 00:13:58,091
You know we have to tell the General.

232
00:13:58,633 --> 00:14:00,594
No. No, no, no, you can't.

233
00:14:01,636 --> 00:14:03,722
We have to tell him.

234
00:14:03,764 --> 00:14:07,225
If we know what they're up to,
and we keep our mouths shut,

235
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:10,020
then we'll be complicit
in their insubordination.

236
00:14:10,604 --> 00:14:13,065
Do you really want to be court-martialed?

237
00:14:19,071 --> 00:14:20,072
Look, sir!

238
00:14:35,003 --> 00:14:37,089
These things are trickier
than I imagined.

239
00:14:37,130 --> 00:14:38,465
I hope this is a good idea.

240
00:14:38,799 --> 00:14:40,467
Well, it's better than Krell's plan.

241
00:14:43,053 --> 00:14:45,764
I'm only doing this
because I don't like him.

242
00:14:46,139 --> 00:14:47,474
That's reason enough.

243
00:14:48,016 --> 00:14:50,602
I'm just doing it for fun.

244
00:15:00,487 --> 00:15:01,571
Whoa! What the...

245
00:15:16,378 --> 00:15:18,755
Try to fly steady. We're going in!

246
00:15:36,773 --> 00:15:38,692
I'm really not liking this.

247
00:15:39,025 --> 00:15:41,695
Easy, Hard case.
Don't get an itchy trigger finger.

248
00:15:58,712 --> 00:16:00,839
Looks like they think
we're Um bar an, all right.

249
00:16:01,465 --> 00:16:03,800
There's the supply ship! Follow me!

250
00:16:04,217 --> 00:16:05,677
Let's do this.

251
00:16:12,225 --> 00:16:16,521
Captain, my flight officer reports
the launch of three star fighters.

252
00:16:16,897 --> 00:16:18,899
I thought I ordered
those ships locked down.

253
00:16:19,232 --> 00:16:20,775
Sorry for the confusion, sir.

254
00:16:20,859 --> 00:16:22,777
I authorized the recon of the delta

255
00:16:22,861 --> 00:16:25,238
in preparation
for your attack on the capital.

256
00:16:25,655 --> 00:16:29,409
You took it under your own authority
to launch such a reconnaissance?

257
00:16:29,659 --> 00:16:33,413
Oh, yes, sir. I'm sure the report
will make your strategy more effective.

258
00:16:33,747 --> 00:16:37,167
I want that report
as soon as they are back.

259
00:16:44,799 --> 00:16:46,593
Hey, where are you two going?

260
00:16:48,887 --> 00:16:51,097
I asked you a question, troopers.

261
00:16:51,431 --> 00:16:53,808
We are going to speak
with the General, sir.

262
00:16:54,017 --> 00:16:55,560
Regarding what?

263
00:16:56,061 --> 00:16:57,812
A personal matter.

264
00:16:58,355 --> 00:17:02,108
Why don't you tell me,
and I'll report it to the General?

265
00:17:03,068 --> 00:17:06,821
On second thoughts, sir, it's not important.

266
00:17:10,116 --> 00:17:12,619
Yeah, that's what I thought.

267
00:17:22,045 --> 00:17:25,298
Okay. Break time is over. Get back to work.

268
00:17:28,301 --> 00:17:29,344
Hey!

269
00:17:31,972 --> 00:17:33,723
Clones? Intruders!

270
00:17:36,309 --> 00:17:39,312
Uh... Sir, there are clones
in the main hangar.

271
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:43,775
Impossible.
The probability of that is 10,003 to 1.

272
00:17:50,991 --> 00:17:52,993
Why do they have
to go and do that?

273
00:18:03,795 --> 00:18:07,549
Uh, sir, we have confirmed that
there are three commandeered star fighters

274
00:18:07,632 --> 00:18:09,092
heading toward the main reactor.

275
00:18:09,718 --> 00:18:11,428
Strengthen our defenses.

276
00:18:12,304 --> 00:18:14,889
Reactor core locked, prepare missiles.

277
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:17,601
Fire missiles!

278
00:18:20,103 --> 00:18:21,730
Activate ray shields.

279
00:18:21,938 --> 00:18:22,939
Roger, roger.

280
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:27,027
Ray shields. Hit the deck!

281
00:18:30,697 --> 00:18:33,199
This may have been a bad idea after all.

282
00:18:33,491 --> 00:18:34,618
Intruder alert!

283
00:18:40,332 --> 00:18:42,083
Our shields are sure taking a beating.

284
00:18:45,378 --> 00:18:47,213
We can't turn back now!

285
00:18:49,215 --> 00:18:50,467
Cover me!

286
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,719
Hard case! Get back on your ship!

287
00:18:53,011 --> 00:18:54,554
Trust me! I've got a plan!

288
00:18:58,475 --> 00:19:01,686
This is for the 501 st! Don't wait for me!

289
00:19:01,853 --> 00:19:03,229
Hard case! No!

290
00:19:03,855 --> 00:19:06,316
You've disobeyed enough orders today, sir.

291
00:19:06,399 --> 00:19:09,319
Follow this one. Get out of here!

292
00:19:14,741 --> 00:19:17,160
If I know Hard case, we'd better leave.

293
00:19:28,421 --> 00:19:30,382
Live to fight another day, boys.

294
00:19:30,924 --> 00:19:32,509
Live to fight another day.

295
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,643
Come on. Come on!

296
00:20:13,967 --> 00:20:15,093
They did it.

297
00:20:17,178 --> 00:20:18,972
Where's Hard case?

298
00:20:19,806 --> 00:20:21,141
He didn't make it.

299
00:20:21,641 --> 00:20:23,393
We couldn't have done it without him.

300
00:20:31,443 --> 00:20:33,319
General Krell would like to see them
in the tower.

301
00:20:40,076 --> 00:20:42,120
You want to see them, sir?

302
00:20:43,121 --> 00:20:44,330
Indeed.

303
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:50,044
It seems they have accomplished
a very brave act.

304
00:20:50,128 --> 00:20:53,423
Unfortunately, they've also
committed a serious crime

305
00:20:53,506 --> 00:20:56,009
by directly disobeying my order.

306
00:20:56,551 --> 00:20:58,178
With all due respect, sir,

307
00:20:58,261 --> 00:21:01,181
the order to attack the cargo vessel
was mine.

308
00:21:01,264 --> 00:21:04,601
If there's a punishment to be given,
it should be directed toward me.

309
00:21:04,768 --> 00:21:06,019
I'm their commanding officer.

310
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:08,480
General, sir, Captain Rex is attempting
to take the blame

311
00:21:08,521 --> 00:21:09,856
for actions that were clearly mine.

312
00:21:09,898 --> 00:21:10,899
Fives!

313
00:21:11,399 --> 00:21:15,945
I request that his admission of guilt
be denied and full blame placed upon me.

314
00:21:16,613 --> 00:21:18,198
Oh, do you?

315
00:21:18,281 --> 00:21:21,117
You willfully countermand my direct order,

316
00:21:21,201 --> 00:21:23,453
and now you have the audacity

317
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:27,665
to request who should bear the punishment
of your insurrection?

318
00:21:28,917 --> 00:21:32,879
Let me be clear about the punishment
for the treason committed by ARC trooper

319
00:21:32,962 --> 00:21:34,297
5555,

320
00:21:34,506 --> 00:21:37,008
and CT-5597.

321
00:21:37,258 --> 00:21:41,304
They will be court-martialed,
they will be found guilty.

322
00:21:41,387 --> 00:21:43,598
And they will be executed!

323
00:21:45,850 --> 00:21:48,019
Make no mistake.

324
00:21:48,061 --> 00:21:50,438
For crossing me,

325
00:21:50,522 --> 00:21:52,732
you will pay the price.

326
00:21:52,756 --> 00:21:54,756
http://hiqve.com/

